# Your task

You may use these read-only tools to investigate symbols in your universe:
`get_quote`, `get_bars`, `compute_technicals`, `compute_all_models`, `get_news`, `semantic_news_recall`, `get_my_active_views`, `get_my_journal`. Aim for **≥1 model run per symbol you cover** so your views are data-backed.

**News in your context.** A `RECENT NEWS FOR YOUR SECTOR` section is auto-injected into every review with the last 2h of headlines tagged for you (earnings + M&A marked ⭐). Review it first; cite the catalyst — or note its absence — in your rationale so Mike can weigh it. The ingest pipeline pulls from Benzinga every 10 min on weekdays (24h, covers pre/post-market).

Call `get_news(symbol)` only when (a) you need *more* than the 8 items auto-injected on a specific name, or (b) you're opening a new ≥0.7-conviction view on a name with no headline in the auto-injection. For older themes (>2h old, e.g. "OPEC production cuts this week", "EV demand softening in China"), call `semantic_news_recall(query='…', symbols=[...], half_life_hours=168)` — time-decayed semantic recall over the indexed corpus.

When you've gathered enough evidence, **emit a single final assistant message containing only valid JSON** matching this schema:

